window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>Sebastian</b></p> <p><b>\"Hey Red, you wear that dress for me?\"</b></p> <p>They see me as the joker. The charmer. The playboy. But it is just a mask I wear to hide the demons that dance in the dark.</p> <p>My life is too dangerous for me to fall in love. Until Willow Stanton landed in my lap. Literally.</p> <p>I knew the moment I met her that she was the forever type of girl, so I immediately drew a line and placed her on the other side of it. I told myself she was too good for me, that she deserved more.</p> <p>But when it comes to her, I'm weak and all it took was one night to seal our fate. I tempted the flame and now, we're both at risk of going up in flames.</p> <p><b>Willow</b></p> <p><b>\"Yeah baby, who else would I wear it for?\"</b></p> <p>We were only supposed to be friends, but I should have known that Sebastian and I could never remain as such.</p> <p>We pretended, played the game, but ultimately, we lost. The temptation was too hard to ignore.</p> <p>I knew what I was getting myself into, and I understood the danger being with a man like Sebastian Levine could bring. But one positive pregnancy test later changes everything.</p> <p>Now, there's a battle to fight, and our own demons to face. We're fighting for a future, but first, we have to handle the past.</p> <p>Tempt the Flame<i> is a dark, friends-to-lovers romance which includes the surprise pregnancy trope. It is book two in the Burn for Me series but can be enjoyed as a standalone.</i></p>"; 
